<b>Subject:</b> Easy response<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1818" TARGET=_self>Weren't you the darkelf that whined a bunch when you got looted?</A> (Min)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Amazing change of heart it seems.

<P>Actually, that was my character's response, asking whomever did it to come forward. If they'd been silly
<BR>enough to do so, I would have kept track of their name for future reference. All I lost was a few silver
<BR>and a cloak. My character was bored while rememorizing spells, and it was possible that I might goad
<BR>someone into admitting to the deed. That would have been fun. I don't say that there's anything wrong
<BR>with looting, but I've told people repeatedly that as it's a PvP server, they have to be accepting of the
<BR>concequenses of their actions. But that's a completely different thread from this one. This one is:
<P>Does having the possibility of low level characters getting a lot of cash from looting a another
<BR>character break the game economy?
<P>Do you have anything to add, even more snide remarks, Min????
<P>-Biggles, Cleric of Innoruuk
